{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-detail-page-js","path":"/finding-a-new-role/what-suitable-alternative-employment-means","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Buckinghamshire HR service desk","basePath":"https://bucks-temp-name.com","gaConfig":{"id":"UA-129132977-3"}}},"contentfulPage":{"title":"What suitable alternative employment means","metaTitle":"What suitable alternative employment means","metaDescription":"Find out what is considered suitable alternative employment and when you might be offered it.","parentPage":{"slug":"finding-a-new-role","title":"Employee transfers"},"intro":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"html":"<p>If your current role is being made redundant, you may be offered another role that is similar enough to be considered suitable alternative employment. If you don’t want to accept this you won’t be entitled to a redundancy payment. </p>"}},"body":null,"hero":{"headline":"Finding a new role hero","subHeading":null,"image":[{"title":"Finding a new role image - large","description":"1440","file":{"details":{"size":59227,"image":{"width":1440,"height":450}},"fileName":"employment--1440.jpg","contentType":"image/jpeg","url":"//images.ctfassets.net/fxzi1pcakms5/7nJ99JgnL5qKCnXSiWWhCQ/5521780f38d331a85fa3ee37a496c51d/employment--1440.jpg"}},{"title":"Finding a new role - medium","description":"800","file":{"details":{"size":32247,"image":{"width":800,"height":375}},"fileName":"employment--800.jpg","contentType":"image/jpeg","url":"//images.ctfassets.net/fxzi1pcakms5/7IEqxCJH9lHITN3EcGQeNJ/e17b6974a248edfb04b72283ac074bf3/employment--800.jpg"}},{"title":"Finding a new role - small","description":"440","file":{"details":{"size":16781,"image":{"width":440,"height":300}},"fileName":"employment--440.jpg","contentType":"image/jpeg","url":"//images.ctfassets.net/fxzi1pcakms5/5Gur66Zsnjs9j1Wgelb5zq/2dff65672c0a517ed995f9364c4ac631/employment--440.jpg"}}]},"collapsibleLinks":[{"title":"What counts as suitable alternative employment?","ariaLabel":null,"content":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Suitable alternative employment has to be broadly similar to your previous role in terms of duties and responsibilities, how much you’re paid and where you’ll work. The terms and conditions can’t be substantially worse for you than your current ones. </p>\n<p>All these points are considered:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Salary</li>\n<li>Conditions of employment</li>\n<li>Duties and responsibilities</li>\n<li>Location</li>\n<li>Skills, knowledge and experience</li>\n<li>Aptitude and potential</li>\n<li>Training and re-training opportunities</li>\n<li>Special individual circumstances</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you want to apply for jobs at a higher level, you’ll go through the normal recruitment process rather than automatically getting an interview if you meet the essential criteria.</p>"}},"open":null,"link":null,"mediaLink":null},{"title":"Going onto a fixed term contract","ariaLabel":null,"content":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"html":"<p>If you’ve been on a permanent contract, you may be offered a fixed term contract, and this will be considered a suitable alternative employment. We would typically use a fixed term contract to keep you working here while we try to find another permanent role. </p>\n<p>After taking a fixed term contract, you can rejoin the register once you’ve been served notice. If you can’t find another role at that point you’ll receive your redundancy pay.</p>"}},"open":null,"link":null,"mediaLink":null},{"title":"If you say no to a role","ariaLabel":null,"content":{"childMarkdownRemark":{"html":"<p>If you don’t want to take the suitable alternative employment you’re offered, refuse an interview for a role, or resign without good reason during a trial period, you may lose any redundancy pay you would have been owed. </p>\n<p>Your manager will meet with you to find out your reasons (you can be accompanied by a trade union representative or a colleague). If they conclude that you’ve unreasonably refused the role, you’ll lose your redundancy entitlement.</p>"}},"open":null,"link":null,"mediaLink":null}],"mediaLink":null}},"pageContext":{"id":"9e94d6f2-39a1-5bb7-b5d8-2fbff9dfbd1c","map":{"510eff4f-2b1f-5b23-a329-8c19f43773ed":"holidays-and-time-off/annual-leave","d95dbc68-e229-5dd8-8a67-de32e90c3a11":"training-and-development/step-up-to-social-work","930fdc5f-ac67-506f-b847-6229569bf26a":"your-performance-at-work/your-performance-review","bead0121-d209-5eaa-907c-d64ca7a314a5":"training-and-development/upskilling-apprenticeships","458dc126-bc87-5700-af41-d7b61aff4a95":"training-and-development/new-talent-apprenticeships","a7172d78-188e-59fb-81f1-d49b18ca1979":"training-and-development/on-demand-management-apprenticeship-programmes","0e7a6481-b2c7-574e-80a0-34aa1f8cd8d3":"how-we-recruit-people/getting-approval-to-recruit","66fa88ab-b900-555e-8deb-1e53b41d3814":"how-we-recruit-people/recruiting-agency-workers","6acbf4fa-7b21-51d3-a267-f060cf1d9dbf":"values-at-work/trustworthy","ba96fa6d-873b-5756-91f0-3a4b38158e5f":"values-at-work/collaborative","fefbbb2a-1c8e-5761-acf3-e53d689d6d83":"values-at-work/ambitious","6ba63441-c932-5f9c-8eed-8fb0f307ab7d":"values-at-work/proud","9dcc0517-92be-542d-9822-655116289c9d":"how-we-recruit-people/interviews-and-assessments","c46f43ce-d8cb-585c-861a-8def520a0959":"behaviour-at-work/how-to-behave-at-work","39198378-94af-5580-baa0-448145109df1":"your-performance-at-work/reviewing-and-setting-goals","bca5694c-e81e-5c4d-8201-e3e5bb2104be":"how-we-recruit-people/what-to-do-before-the-new-person-starts","0de22c92-8efc-5818-a53f-5683badc699d":"pay-money/new-starters-and-p45","d2dde659-6599-5a20-959e-273206ac186c":"how-we-recruit-people/safer-recruiting","7d31c1d3-4eff-576d-bc56-67655c0d2072":"time-off-sick/long-term-illness","faf2d81e-c32e-592a-9c42-a8e05c808176":"behaviour-at-work/if-you-have-a-problem-at-work","1b06279f-e6c6-58e3-ba24-9633a33de0b7":"behaviour-at-work/poor-behaviour","7f6300a2-de75-5c16-ba3c-27f436de1f60":"your-performance-at-work/mandato